[{"ts":1757953850278,"type":"say","say":"text","text":"**Mission**: With the **same attachments** I just provided (latest scripts, 3 newest logs, and 5 processing-state snapshots), perform a full audit to determine **what of the mainplan.md ( in root folder)\n  integrated, what’s missing, what regressed**, and why the system **skips product extraction after the 2-step filter** and **zeros category indices across runs**. Produce a surgical\n  implementation plan with diffs and a test protocol.\n\n  ## 📦 Inputs (use these exact files)\n\n  **Scripts**\n\n  * `/passive_extraction_workflow_latest.py`\n  * `/fixed_enhanced_state_manager.py`\n\n  **Latest logs (3)**\n\n  * `/run_custom_poundwholesale_20250915_192612.log`\n  * `/run_custom_poundwholesale_20250915_193138.log`\n  * `/run_custom_poundwholesale_20250915_193648.log`\n\n  **Processing state snapshots (5)**\n\n  * `/1strun.json`\n  * `/start2ndrun.json`\n  * `/endof2ndrun.json`\n  * `/during 3rdrun.json`\n  * `/poundwholesale_co_uk_processing_state.json` (final/latest)\n\n  **Reference MDs (for citations in code comments)**\n\n  * `/.serena/memories/comprehensive_legacy_processing_and_phase_detection_analysis_report.md`\n  * `/.serena/memories/surgical_implementation_guide_with_complete_analysis.md`\n\n  **Reference: Set-1 tasks (from the prior plan) — treat these as acceptance targets**\n\n  * Remove category off-by-one at init\n  * Phase detection must compare **file** counts (not “session/global” placeholders)\n  * Cache selection fallback (largest valid array if “current” is implausibly small)\n  * Amazon progress commits use `total_cats=1`\n  * Display index clamp\n  * Keep resume proof banners\n  * OpenAI key non-fatal when AI disabled\n\n  **Critical behaviors to verify/repair (reported regressions)**\n\n  1. **Post-filter skip**: After 2-step filtering shows work (e.g., `NEEDS_FULL_EXTRACTION (6)`), system **skips extraction** and jumps to next category\n  2. **Resume/index persistence**: Category index appears to **zero at each run start**; no stable continuation across runs; pointer “flicker” when a category has no work\n\n  ---\n\n  ## 🧪 What to Prove/Disprove (Hypotheses Checklist)\n\n  **H1. Deprecated writer still in use → no per-product persistence**\n\n  * ❗️If any call to `state_manager.update_processing_index(...)` exists, it is a **no-op** (the method is intentionally disabled) → product index & resumption **never** advance; resume guard later skips.\n  * ✅ Expected fix: **Only** `commit_supplier_progress(...)` and `commit_amazon_progress(...)` write state.\n\n  **H2. Category pointer written at “init” (eager) instead of “progress/complete”**\n\n  * If workflow sets `current_category_index` during **initialization** (or still uses `initialize_category_processing(category_index - 1)`), pointer can jump prematurely and cause `📋 Resume skip: category\n  0 < 1 (no work)` despite work being present.\n\n  **H3. Freeze happens after resume gating**\n\n  * If resume check runs **before** `set_frozen_denominator(...)`, state manager emits `RESUME PTR suppressed: category_denominator_unfrozen` and pointers are unreliable.\n\n  **H4. Method name typo prevents completion bookkeeping**\n\n  * Workflow calls `mark_category_complete(...)` but state manager defines `mark_category_completed(...)`. If mismatched → no “done” bookkeeping.\n\n  **H5. Amazon progress totals inconsistent**\n\n  * Any `commit_amazon_progress(..., total_cats≠1, ...)` still exists → misleading progress.\n\n  **H6. Phase detection still uses placeholder counts**\n\n  * Divergence banner still shows `(session: X, global: Y)` instead of file-grounded counts.\n\n  ---\n\n  ## 🛠️ Step-By-Step Audit (do all)\n\n  ### A) Static code scan (both files)\n\n  1. **Grep gates (must run all):**\n\n     * `rg -n \"update_processing_index\\\\(\" /*.py` → **expect 0 hits**\n     * `rg -n \"commit_supplier_progress\\\\(\" /passive_extraction_workflow_latest.py` → **hits present**\n     * `rg -n \"commit_amazon_progress\\\\(.*total_cats=\" /passive{
